\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\nu}_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\nu}_{2}$
\end_inset

.
 This utility is defined as follows
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\mathscr{U}(\bar{\nu}_{1},\bar{\nu}_{2}) & =\beta u_{1}(\bar{\nu}_{1},\bar{\nu}_{2})+(1-\beta)u_{2}(\bar{\nu}_{1},\bar{\nu}_{2})
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For simplcity, we define 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathscr{U}\equiv\mathscr{U}(\bar{\nu}_{1},\bar{\nu}_{2})$
