\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial L}{\partial x}=\frac{\partial L}{\partial y}=\frac{\partial L}{\partial\lambda}=0$
\end_inset

).
 Using FOC under these conditions 
\begin_inset Formula $L=f(x,y)+\lambda(2-x)$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial L}{\partial x}=2x-\lambda$
\end_inset

 leads to 
\begin_inset Formula $2x=\lambda$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $x=2$
\end_inset

.
